# Line-ending normalization — see hub/standards/agent-tooling.md (line-ending hygiene).
# Git stores LF; the working tree checks out LF on every platform regardless of each
# machine's core.autocrlf, so LF-expecting tooling stops flagging phantom "modified"
# files. This repo authors from Windows (PowerShell), so the guard matters here.

# Default: auto-detect text vs binary; force LF in the working tree everywhere.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows scripts must stay CRLF or they break.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf

# SVG is text (diff/merge it), but keep it explicit.
*.svg text

# Binary assets — never touch EOLs (belt-and-suspenders; text=auto already detects most).
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.webp binary
*.ico  binary
*.icns binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.eot binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.gz  binary
*.mp4  binary
*.webm binary
*.mov  binary
*.mp3  binary
*.wav  binary
